{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I admit that I'm a little bit nervous here"},{"time":3000,"text":"because I'm going to say some radical things,"},{"time":6000,"text":"about how we should think about cancer differently,"},{"time":9000,"text":"to an audience that contains a lot of people"},{"time":11000,"text":"who know a lot more about cancer than I do."},{"time":15000,"text":"But I will also contest that I'm not as nervous as I should be"},{"time":18000,"text":"because I'm pretty sure I'm right about this."},{"time":20000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":22000,"text":"And that this, in fact, will be"},{"time":24000,"text":"the way that we treat cancer in the future."},{"time":28000,"text":"In order to talk about cancer,"},{"time":30000,"text":"I'm going to actually have to --"},{"time":33000,"text":"let me get the big slide here."},{"time":38000,"text":"First, I'm going to try to give you a different perspective of genomics."},{"time":41000,"text":"I want to put it in perspective of the bigger picture"},{"time":43000,"text":"of all the other things that are going on --"},{"time":46000,"text":"and then talk about something you haven't heard so much about, which is proteomics."},{"time":49000,"text":"Having explained those,"},{"time":51000,"text":"that will set up for what I think will be a different idea"},{"time":54000,"text":"about how to go about treating cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"So let me start with genomics."},{"time":58000,"text":"It is the hot topic."},{"time":60000,"text":"It is the place where we're learning the most."},{"time":62000,"text":"This is the great frontier."},{"time":64000,"text":"But it has its limitations."},{"time":67000,"text":"And in particular, you've probably all heard the analogy"},{"time":70000,"text":"that the genome is like the blueprint of your body,"},{"time":73000,"text":"and if that were only true, it would be great,"},{"time":75000,"text":"but it's not."},{"time":77000,"text":"It's like the parts list of your body."},{"time":79000,"text":"It doesn't say how things are connected,"},{"time":81000,"text":"what causes what and so on."},{"time":84000,"text":"So if I can make an analogy,"},{"time":86000,"text":"let's say that you were trying to tell the difference"},{"time":88000,"text":"between a good restaurant, a healthy restaurant"},{"time":91000,"text":"and a sick restaurant,"},{"time":93000,"text":"and all you had was the list of ingredients"},{"time":95000,"text":"that they had in their larder."},{"time":98000,"text":"So it might be that, if you went to a French restaurant"},{"time":101000,"text":"and you looked through it and you found"},{"time":103000,"text":"they only had margarine and they didn't have butter,"},{"time":105000,"text":"you could say, \"Ah, I see what's wrong with them."},{"time":107000,"text":"I can make them healthy.\""},{"time":109000,"text":"And there probably are special cases of that."},{"time":111000,"text":"You could certainly tell the difference"},{"time":113000,"text":"between a Chinese restaurant and a French restaurant"},{"time":115000,"text":"by what they had in a larder."},{"time":117000,"text":"So the list of ingredients does tell you something,"},{"time":120000,"text":"and sometimes it tells you something that's wrong."},{"time":124000,"text":"If they have tons of salt,"},{"time":126000,"text":"you might guess they're using too much salt, or something like that."},{"time":129000,"text":"But it's limited,"},{"time":131000,"text":"because really to know if it's a healthy restaurant,"},{"time":133000,"text":"you need to taste the food, you need to know what goes on in the kitchen,"},{"time":136000,"text":"you need the product of all of those ingredients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"So if I look at a person"},{"time":141000,"text":"and I look at a person's genome, it's the same thing."},{"time":144000,"text":"The part of the genome that we can read"},{"time":146000,"text":"is the list of ingredients."},{"time":148000,"text":"And so indeed,"},{"time":150000,"text":"there are times when we can find ingredients"},{"time":152000,"text":"that [are] bad."},{"time":154000,"text":"Cystic fibrosis is an example of a disease"},{"time":156000,"text":"where you just have a bad ingredient and you have a disease,"},{"time":159000,"text":"and we can actually make a direct correspondence"},{"time":162000,"text":"between the ingredient and the disease."},{"time":165000,"text":"But most things, you really have to know what's going on in the kitchen,"},{"time":168000,"text":"because, mostly, sick people used to be healthy people --"},{"time":170000,"text":"they have the same genome."},{"time":172000,"text":"So the genome really tells you much more"},{"time":174000,"text":"about predisposition."},{"time":176000,"text":"So what you can tell"},{"time":178000,"text":"is you can tell the difference between an Asian person and a European person"},{"time":180000,"text":"by looking at their ingredients list."},{"time":182000,"text":"But you really for the most part can't tell the difference"},{"time":185000,"text":"between a healthy person and a sick person --"},{"time":188000,"text":"except in some of these special cases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190000,"text":"So why all the big deal"},{"time":192000,"text":"about genetics?"},{"time":194000,"text":"Well first of all,"},{"time":196000,"text":"it's because we can read it, which is fantastic."},{"time":199000,"text":"It is very useful in certain circumstances."},{"time":202000,"text":"It's also the great theoretical triumph"},{"time":205000,"text":"of biology."},{"time":207000,"text":"It's the one theory"},{"time":209000,"text":"that the biologists ever really got right."},{"time":211000,"text":"It's fundamental to Darwin"},{"time":213000,"text":"and Mendel and so on."},{"time":215000,"text":"And so it's the one thing where they predicted a theoretical construct."},{"time":219000,"text":"So Mendel had this idea of a gene"},{"time":221000,"text":"as an abstract thing,"},{"time":224000,"text":"and Darwin built a whole theory"},{"time":226000,"text":"that depended on them existing,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and then Watson and Crick"},{"time":230000,"text":"actually looked and found one."},{"time":232000,"text":"So this happens in physics all the time."},{"time":234000,"text":"You predict a black hole,"},{"time":236000,"text":"and you look out the telescope and there it is, just like you said."},{"time":239000,"text":"But it rarely happens in biology."},{"time":241000,"text":"So this great triumph -- it's so good,"},{"time":244000,"text":"there's almost a religious experience"},{"time":246000,"text":"in biology."},{"time":248000,"text":"And Darwinian evolution"},{"time":250000,"text":"is really the core theory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"So the other reason it's been very popular"},{"time":257000,"text":"is because we can measure it, it's digital."},{"time":260000,"text":"And in fact,"},{"time":262000,"text":"thanks to Kary Mullis,"},{"time":264000,"text":"you can basically measure your genome in your kitchen"},{"time":268000,"text":"with a few extra ingredients."},{"time":271000,"text":"So for instance, by measuring the genome,"},{"time":274000,"text":"we've learned a lot about how we're related to other kinds of animals"},{"time":278000,"text":"by the closeness of our genome,"},{"time":281000,"text":"or how we're related to each other -- the family tree,"},{"time":284000,"text":"or the tree of life."},{"time":286000,"text":"There's a huge amount of information about the genetics"},{"time":289000,"text":"just by comparing the genetic similarity."},{"time":292000,"text":"Now of course, in medical application,"},{"time":294000,"text":"that is very useful"},{"time":296000,"text":"because it's the same kind of information"},{"time":299000,"text":"that the doctor gets from your family medical history --"},{"time":302000,"text":"except probably,"},{"time":304000,"text":"your genome knows much more about your medical history than you do."},{"time":307000,"text":"And so by reading the genome,"},{"time":309000,"text":"we can find out much more about your family than you probably know."},{"time":312000,"text":"And so we can discover things"},{"time":314000,"text":"that probably you could have found"},{"time":316000,"text":"by looking at enough of your relatives,"},{"time":318000,"text":"but they may be surprising."},{"time":321000,"text":"I did the 23andMe thing"},{"time":323000,"text":"and was very surprised to discover that I am fat and bald."},{"time":326000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":333000,"text":"But sometimes you can learn much more useful things about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"But mostly"},{"time":339000,"text":"what you need to know, to find out if you're sick,"},{"time":341000,"text":"is not your predispositions,"},{"time":343000,"text":"but it's actually what's going on in your body right now."},{"time":346000,"text":"So to do that, what you really need to do,"},{"time":348000,"text":"you need to look at the things"},{"time":350000,"text":"that the genes are producing"},{"time":352000,"text":"and what's happening after the genetics,"},{"time":354000,"text":"and that's what proteomics is about."},{"time":356000,"text":"Just like genome mixes the study of all the genes,"},{"time":359000,"text":"proteomics is the study of all the proteins."},{"time":362000,"text":"And the proteins are all of the little things in your body"},{"time":364000,"text":"that are signaling between the cells --"},{"time":367000,"text":"actually, the machines that are operating --"},{"time":369000,"text":"that's where the action is."},{"time":371000,"text":"Basically, a human body"},{"time":374000,"text":"is a conversation going on,"},{"time":377000,"text":"both within the cells and between the cells,"},{"time":380000,"text":"and they're telling each other to grow and to die,"},{"time":383000,"text":"and when you're sick,"},{"time":385000,"text":"something's gone wrong with that conversation."},{"time":387000,"text":"And so the trick is --"},{"time":389000,"text":"unfortunately, we don't have an easy way to measure these"},{"time":392000,"text":"like we can measure the genome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394000,"text":"So the problem is that measuring --"},{"time":397000,"text":"if you try to measure all the proteins, it's a very elaborate process."},{"time":400000,"text":"It requires hundreds of steps,"},{"time":402000,"text":"and it takes a long, long time."},{"time":404000,"text":"And it matters how much of the protein it is."},{"time":406000,"text":"It could be very significant that a protein changed by 10 percent,"},{"time":409000,"text":"so it's not a nice digital thing like DNA."},{"time":412000,"text":"And basically our problem is somebody's in the middle"},{"time":414000,"text":"of this very long stage,"},{"time":416000,"text":"they pause for just a moment,"},{"time":418000,"text":"and they leave something in an enzyme for a second,"},{"time":420000,"text":"and all of a sudden all the measurements from then on"},{"time":422000,"text":"don't work."},{"time":424000,"text":"And so then people get very inconsistent results"},{"time":426000,"text":"when they do it this way."},{"time":428000,"text":"People have tried very hard to do this."},{"time":430000,"text":"I tried this a couple of times"},{"time":432000,"text":"and looked at this problem and gave up on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434000,"text":"I kept getting this call from this oncologist"},{"time":436000,"text":"named David Agus."},{"time":438000,"text":"And Applied Minds gets a lot of calls"},{"time":441000,"text":"from people who want help with their problems,"},{"time":443000,"text":"and I didn't think this was a very likely one to call back,"},{"time":446000,"text":"so I kept on giving him to the delay list."},{"time":449000,"text":"And then one day,"},{"time":451000,"text":"I get a call from John Doerr, Bill Berkman"},{"time":453000,"text":"and Al Gore on the same day"},{"time":455000,"text":"saying return David Agus's phone call."},{"time":457000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":459000,"text":"So I was like, \"Okay. This guy's at least resourceful.\""},{"time":461000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":465000,"text":"So we started talking,"},{"time":467000,"text":"and he said, \"I really need a better way to measure proteins.\""},{"time":470000,"text":"I'm like, \"Looked at that. Been there."},{"time":472000,"text":"Not going to be easy.\""},{"time":474000,"text":"He's like, \"No, no. I really need it."},{"time":476000,"text":"I mean, I see patients dying every day"},{"time":480000,"text":"because we don't know what's going on inside of them."},{"time":483000,"text":"We have to have a window into this.\""},{"time":485000,"text":"And he took me through"},{"time":487000,"text":"specific examples of when he really needed it."},{"time":490000,"text":"And I realized, wow, this would really make a big difference,"},{"time":492000,"text":"if we could do it,"},{"time":494000,"text":"and so I said, \"Well, let's look at it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":496000,"text":"Applied Minds has enough play money"},{"time":498000,"text":"that we can go and just work on something"},{"time":500000,"text":"without getting anybody's funding or permission or anything."},{"time":503000,"text":"So we started playing around with this."},{"time":505000,"text":"And as we did it, we realized this was the basic problem --"},{"time":508000,"text":"that taking the sip of coffee --"},{"time":510000,"text":"that there were humans doing this complicated process"},{"time":512000,"text":"and that what really needed to be done"},{"time":514000,"text":"was to automate this process like an assembly line"},{"time":517000,"text":"and build robots"},{"time":519000,"text":"that would measure proteomics."},{"time":521000,"text":"And so we did that,"},{"time":523000,"text":"and working with David,"},{"time":525000,"text":"we made a little company called Applied Proteomics eventually,"},{"time":528000,"text":"which makes this robotic assembly line,"},{"time":531000,"text":"which, in a very consistent way, measures the protein."},{"time":534000,"text":"And I'll show you what that protein measurement looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538000,"text":"Basically, what we do"},{"time":540000,"text":"is we take a drop of blood"},{"time":542000,"text":"out of a patient,"},{"time":544000,"text":"and we sort out the proteins"},{"time":546000,"text":"in the drop of blood"},{"time":548000,"text":"according to how much they weigh,"},{"time":550000,"text":"how slippery they are,"},{"time":552000,"text":"and we arrange them in an image."},{"time":555000,"text":"And so we can look at literally"},{"time":557000,"text":"hundreds of thousands of features at once"},{"time":559000,"text":"out of that drop of blood."},{"time":561000,"text":"And we can take a different one tomorrow,"},{"time":563000,"text":"and you will see your proteins tomorrow will be different --"},{"time":565000,"text":"they'll be different after you eat or after you sleep."},{"time":568000,"text":"They really tell us what's going on there."},{"time":571000,"text":"And so this picture,"},{"time":573000,"text":"which looks like a big smudge to you,"},{"time":575000,"text":"is actually the thing that got me really thrilled about this"},{"time":579000,"text":"and made me feel like we were on the right track."},{"time":581000,"text":"So if I zoom into that picture,"},{"time":583000,"text":"I can just show you what it means."},{"time":585000,"text":"We sort out the proteins -- from left to right"},{"time":588000,"text":"is the weight of the fragments that we're getting,"},{"time":591000,"text":"and from top to bottom is how slippery they are."},{"time":594000,"text":"So we're zooming in here just to show you a little bit of it."},{"time":597000,"text":"And so each of these lines"},{"time":599000,"text":"represents some signal that we're getting out of a piece of a protein."},{"time":602000,"text":"And you can see how the lines occur"},{"time":604000,"text":"in these little groups of bump, bump, bump, bump, bump."},{"time":608000,"text":"And that's because we're measuring the weight so precisely that --"},{"time":611000,"text":"carbon comes in different isotopes,"},{"time":613000,"text":"so if it has an extra neutron on it,"},{"time":616000,"text":"we actually measure it as a different chemical."},{"time":620000,"text":"So we're actually measuring each isotope as a different one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"And so that gives you an idea"},{"time":626000,"text":"of how exquisitely sensitive this is."},{"time":628000,"text":"So seeing this picture"},{"time":630000,"text":"is sort of like getting to be Galileo"},{"time":632000,"text":"and looking at the stars"},{"time":634000,"text":"and looking through the telescope for the first time,"},{"time":636000,"text":"and suddenly you say, \"Wow, it's way more complicated than we thought it was.\""},{"time":639000,"text":"But we can see that stuff out there"},{"time":641000,"text":"and actually see features of it."},{"time":643000,"text":"So this is the signature out of which we're trying to get patterns."},{"time":646000,"text":"So what we do with this"},{"time":648000,"text":"is, for example, we can look at two patients,"},{"time":650000,"text":"one that responded to a drug and one that didn't respond to a drug,"},{"time":653000,"text":"and ask, \"What's going on differently"},{"time":655000,"text":"inside of them?\""},{"time":657000,"text":"And so we can make these measurements precisely enough"},{"time":660000,"text":"that we can overlay two patients and look at the differences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"So here we have Alice in green"},{"time":665000,"text":"and Bob in red."},{"time":667000,"text":"We overlay them. This is actual data."},{"time":670000,"text":"And you can see, mostly it overlaps and it's yellow,"},{"time":673000,"text":"but there's some things that just Alice has"},{"time":675000,"text":"and some things that just Bob has."},{"time":677000,"text":"And if we find a pattern of things"},{"time":680000,"text":"of the responders to the drug,"},{"time":683000,"text":"we see that in the blood,"},{"time":685000,"text":"they have the condition"},{"time":687000,"text":"that allows them to respond to this drug."},{"time":689000,"text":"We might not even know what this protein is,"},{"time":691000,"text":"but we can see it's a marker"},{"time":693000,"text":"for the response to the disease."},{"time":698000,"text":"So this already, I think,"},{"time":700000,"text":"is tremendously useful in all kinds of medicine."},{"time":703000,"text":"But I think this is actually"},{"time":705000,"text":"just the beginning"},{"time":707000,"text":"of how we're going to treat cancer."},{"time":709000,"text":"So let me move to cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711000,"text":"The thing about cancer --"},{"time":713000,"text":"when I got into this,"},{"time":715000,"text":"I really knew nothing about it,"},{"time":717000,"text":"but working with David Agus,"},{"time":719000,"text":"I started watching how cancer was actually being treated"},{"time":722000,"text":"and went to operations where it was being cut out."},{"time":725000,"text":"And as I looked at it,"},{"time":727000,"text":"to me it didn't make sense"},{"time":729000,"text":"how we were approaching cancer,"},{"time":731000,"text":"and in order to make sense of it,"},{"time":734000,"text":"I had to learn where did this come from."},{"time":737000,"text":"We're treating cancer almost like it's an infectious disease."},{"time":741000,"text":"We're treating it as something that got inside of you"},{"time":743000,"text":"that we have to kill."},{"time":745000,"text":"So this is the great paradigm."},{"time":747000,"text":"This is another case"},{"time":749000,"text":"where a theoretical paradigm in biology really worked --"},{"time":751000,"text":"was the germ theory of disease."},{"time":754000,"text":"So what doctors are mostly trained to do"},{"time":756000,"text":"is diagnose --"},{"time":758000,"text":"that is, put you into a category"},{"time":760000,"text":"and apply a scientifically proven treatment"},{"time":762000,"text":"for that diagnosis --"},{"time":764000,"text":"and that works great for infectious diseases."},{"time":767000,"text":"So if we put you in the category"},{"time":769000,"text":"of you've got syphilis, we can give you penicillin."},{"time":772000,"text":"We know that that works."},{"time":774000,"text":"If you've got malaria, we give you quinine"},{"time":776000,"text":"or some derivative of it."},{"time":778000,"text":"And so that's the basic thing doctors are trained to do,"},{"time":781000,"text":"and it's miraculous"},{"time":783000,"text":"in the case of infectious disease --"},{"time":786000,"text":"how well it works."},{"time":788000,"text":"And many people in this audience probably wouldn't be alive"},{"time":791000,"text":"if doctors didn't do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793000,"text":"But now let's apply that"},{"time":795000,"text":"to systems diseases like cancer."},{"time":797000,"text":"The problem is that, in cancer,"},{"time":799000,"text":"there isn't something else"},{"time":801000,"text":"that's inside of you."},{"time":803000,"text":"It's you; you're broken."},{"time":805000,"text":"That conversation inside of you"},{"time":809000,"text":"got mixed up in some way."},{"time":811000,"text":"So how do we diagnose that conversation?"},{"time":813000,"text":"Well, right now what we do is we divide it by part of the body --"},{"time":816000,"text":"you know, where did it appear? --"},{"time":819000,"text":"and we put you in different categories"},{"time":821000,"text":"according to the part of the body."},{"time":823000,"text":"And then we do a clinical trial"},{"time":825000,"text":"for a drug for lung cancer"},{"time":827000,"text":"and one for prostate cancer and one for breast cancer,"},{"time":830000,"text":"and we treat these as if they're separate diseases"},{"time":833000,"text":"and that this way of dividing them"},{"time":835000,"text":"had something to do with what actually went wrong."},{"time":837000,"text":"And of course, it really doesn't have that much to do"},{"time":839000,"text":"with what went wrong"},{"time":841000,"text":"because cancer is a failure of the system."},{"time":844000,"text":"And in fact, I think we're even wrong"},{"time":846000,"text":"when we talk about cancer as a thing."},{"time":849000,"text":"I think this is the big mistake."},{"time":851000,"text":"I think cancer should not be a noun."},{"time":855000,"text":"We should talk about cancering"},{"time":857000,"text":"as something we do, not something we have."},{"time":860000,"text":"And so those tumors,"},{"time":862000,"text":"those are symptoms of cancer."},{"time":864000,"text":"And so your body is probably cancering all the time,"},{"time":867000,"text":"but there are lots of systems in your body"},{"time":870000,"text":"that keep it under control."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872000,"text":"And so to give you an idea"},{"time":874000,"text":"of an analogy of what I mean"},{"time":876000,"text":"by thinking of cancering as a verb,"},{"time":879000,"text":"imagine we didn't know anything about plumbing,"},{"time":882000,"text":"and the way that we talked about it,"},{"time":884000,"text":"we'd come home and we'd find a leak in our kitchen"},{"time":887000,"text":"and we'd say, \"Oh, my house has water.\""},{"time":891000,"text":"We might divide it -- the plumber would say, \"Well, where's the water?\""},{"time":894000,"text":"\"Well, it's in the kitchen.\" \"Oh, you must have kitchen water.\""},{"time":897000,"text":"That's kind of the level at which it is."},{"time":900000,"text":"\"Kitchen water,"},{"time":902000,"text":"well, first of all, we'll go in there and we'll mop out a lot of it."},{"time":904000,"text":"And then we know that if we sprinkle Drano around the kitchen,"},{"time":907000,"text":"that helps."},{"time":910000,"text":"Whereas living room water,"},{"time":912000,"text":"it's better to do tar on the roof.\""},{"time":914000,"text":"And it sounds silly,"},{"time":916000,"text":"but that's basically what we do."},{"time":918000,"text":"And I'm not saying you shouldn't mop up your water if you have cancer,"},{"time":921000,"text":"but I'm saying that's not really the problem;"},{"time":924000,"text":"that's the symptom of the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":926000,"text":"What we really need to get at"},{"time":928000,"text":"is the process that's going on,"},{"time":930000,"text":"and that's happening at the level"},{"time":932000,"text":"of the proteonomic actions,"},{"time":934000,"text":"happening at the level of why is your body not healing itself"},{"time":937000,"text":"in the way that it normally does?"},{"time":939000,"text":"Because normally, your body is dealing with this problem all the time."},{"time":942000,"text":"So your house is dealing with leaks all the time,"},{"time":945000,"text":"but it's fixing them. It's draining them out and so on."},{"time":949000,"text":"So what we need"},{"time":952000,"text":"is to have a causative model"},{"time":956000,"text":"of what's actually going on,"},{"time":958000,"text":"and proteomics actually gives us"},{"time":961000,"text":"the ability to build a model like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":964000,"text":"David got me invited"},{"time":966000,"text":"to give a talk at National Cancer Institute"},{"time":968000,"text":"and Anna Barker was there."},{"time":972000,"text":"And so I gave this talk"},{"time":974000,"text":"and said, \"Why don't you guys do this?\""},{"time":977000,"text":"And Anna said,"},{"time":979000,"text":"\"Because nobody within cancer"},{"time":982000,"text":"would look at it this way."},{"time":984000,"text":"But what we're going to do, is we're going to create a program"},{"time":987000,"text":"for people outside the field of cancer"},{"time":989000,"text":"to get together with doctors"},{"time":991000,"text":"who really know about cancer"},{"time":994000,"text":"and work out different programs of research.\""},{"time":998000,"text":"So David and I applied to this program"},{"time":1000000,"text":"and created a consortium"},{"time":1002000,"text":"at USC"},{"time":1004000,"text":"where we've got some of the best oncologists in the world"},{"time":1007000,"text":"and some of the best biologists in the world,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"from Cold Spring Harbor,"},{"time":1012000,"text":"Stanford, Austin --"},{"time":1014000,"text":"I won't even go through and name all the places --"},{"time":1017000,"text":"to have a research project"},{"time":1020000,"text":"that will last for five years"},{"time":1022000,"text":"where we're really going to try to build a model of cancer like this."},{"time":1025000,"text":"We're doing it in mice first,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"and we will kill a lot of mice"},{"time":1029000,"text":"in the process of doing this,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"but they will die for a good cause."},{"time":1033000,"text":"And we will actually try to get to the point"},{"time":1036000,"text":"where we have a predictive model"},{"time":1038000,"text":"where we can understand,"},{"time":1040000,"text":"when cancer happens,"},{"time":1042000,"text":"what's actually happening in there"},{"time":1044000,"text":"and which treatment will treat that cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1047000,"text":"So let me just end with giving you a little picture"},{"time":1050000,"text":"of what I think cancer treatment will be like in the future."},{"time":1053000,"text":"So I think eventually,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"once we have one of these models for people,"},{"time":1057000,"text":"which we'll get eventually --"},{"time":1059000,"text":"I mean, our group won't get all the way there --"},{"time":1061000,"text":"but eventually we'll have a very good computer model --"},{"time":1064000,"text":"sort of like a global climate model for weather."},{"time":1067000,"text":"It has lots of different information"},{"time":1070000,"text":"about what's the process going on in this proteomic conversation"},{"time":1073000,"text":"on many different scales."},{"time":1075000,"text":"And so we will simulate"},{"time":1077000,"text":"in that model"},{"time":1079000,"text":"for your particular cancer --"},{"time":1082000,"text":"and this also will be for ALS,"},{"time":1084000,"text":"or any kind of system neurodegenerative diseases,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"things like that --"},{"time":1089000,"text":"we will simulate"},{"time":1091000,"text":"specifically you,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"not just a generic person,"},{"time":1095000,"text":"but what's actually going on inside you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1097000,"text":"And in that simulation, what we could do"},{"time":1099000,"text":"is design for you specifically"},{"time":1101000,"text":"a sequence of treatments,"},{"time":1103000,"text":"and it might be very gentle treatments, very small amounts of drugs."},{"time":1106000,"text":"It might be things like, don't eat that day,"},{"time":1109000,"text":"or give them a little chemotherapy,"},{"time":1111000,"text":"maybe a little radiation."},{"time":1113000,"text":"Of course, we'll do surgery sometimes and so on."},{"time":1116000,"text":"But design a program of treatments specifically for you"},{"time":1119000,"text":"and help your body"},{"time":1122000,"text":"guide back to health --"},{"time":1125000,"text":"guide your body back to health."},{"time":1127000,"text":"Because your body will do most of the work of fixing it"},{"time":1131000,"text":"if we just sort of prop it up in the ways that are wrong."},{"time":1134000,"text":"We put it in the equivalent of splints."},{"time":1136000,"text":"And so your body basically has lots and lots of mechanisms"},{"time":1138000,"text":"for fixing cancer,"},{"time":1140000,"text":"and we just have to prop those up in the right way"},{"time":1143000,"text":"and get them to do the job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1145000,"text":"And so I believe that this will be the way"},{"time":1147000,"text":"that cancer will be treated in the future."},{"time":1149000,"text":"It's going to require a lot of work,"},{"time":1151000,"text":"a lot of research."},{"time":1153000,"text":"There will be many teams like our team"},{"time":1156000,"text":"that work on this."},{"time":1158000,"text":"But I think eventually,"},{"time":1160000,"text":"we will design for everybody"},{"time":1162000,"text":"a custom treatment for cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1166000,"text":"So thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1168000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}